componentInstanceProperties.value: Invest in an innovative marketplace that’s transforming travel industry hire services

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Hirehood takes the hassle out of travelling, allowing holidaymakers to leave items such as bikes, boards and baby equipment at home, thanks to the convenience of being able to hire these items from Hirehood’s digital platform, with just a few clicks of the button.

Its marketplace platform is the first of its kind in Australia, creating a one-stop shop for people to hire the items they need when they need them.

Hirehood was born out of an idea to create a more convenient way for people to access everything they need when they travel. A case in point is parents travelling with young children (including prams, cots, car seats and more).

Also, surfers, adventurers, and mountain bike riders would love to avoid the overwhelming stress of travelling with bulky, expensive items. And it’s not just for travellers. Hirehood also empowers locals to hire recreational equipment to experience their own backyards.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
In the pilot location, the Tweed Coast of NSW, early traction has seen a 20% MoM growth in customers, with suppliers offering over 300 items for hire and demand-side referrals from nearly 300 accommodation providers (Airbnb hosts, letting agencies, caravan parks and resorts).

After successfully launching in August 2023, Hirehood is gearing up to scale its platform throughout Australia and beyond by continuing to partner with both local hire businesses and accommodation providers in various locations, creating the perfect supply and demand model for its products.

Following the company’s successful pre-seed funding round, they’re now looking to give their community the chance to own a piece in the future of their exciting Australian start-up.

Your investment will help them scale their platform by enhancing their technology, bolstering their onboarding team and increasing their exposure through targeted SEO, marketing and branding.
